{
  "stem": "3952.4",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, these wooden shoes, you walk one day to work and back, you-- you have to tread half of the-- half of the-- how do you call this part?",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Half of the sole, half of the heel you-- is-- is gone.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- and if he catches you, when you came in, he would look at this, at your heels, and if it wasn't straight, he would pick you out and beat you, literally, to death.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Literally to death.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now I must tell a preliminary story before that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- every blockalteste had a [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "A [SPEAKS GERMAN] is what it's called, a servant, a personal servant.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now our lageralteste was a German guy by the name of Oskar, and he lived in the first tent of block number one with two-- two secretaries, also German Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This Oskar, one day I hear they called me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "One Sunday, they called me, Izchak Goldblatt, Izchak Goldblatt.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I'm very scared.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "If they call you by name, that means trouble only.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So what happened, his [NON-ENGLISH], his-- his personal servant is a boy from Sighet, and he knew that I speak English, and they needed some translation for the Salonikan guys.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They needed the chimney and the-- there-- the-- the tent was filling up with smoke.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They couldn't speak one word of German, so I was translating from English to German, and for that, he gave me a little milk, about half a glass of milk on the spot, which was a half a glass of life.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And every Sunday, ever second Sunday, when we were not working, every second Sunday we were off, he would leave his-- his plates, his and the two secretaries' plates for me to wash.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So there would be left a little potato, a little fat.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
